label.value: altered resistance to quaternary ammonium salt antimicrobial agent

value.value: A quaternary ammonium salts resistance phenotype where the frequency, rate, timing, or extent of resistance to quaternary ammonium salts is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: increased resistance to quaternary ammonium salt antimicrobial agent

value.value: An altered resistance to quaternary ammonium salts where the frequency, rate, timing, or extent of resistance to quaternary ammonium salts is increased relative to a designated control.

label.value: decreased resistance to quaternary ammonium salt antimicrobial agent

value.value: An altered resistance to quaternary ammonium salts where the frequency, rate, timing, or extent of resistance to quaternary ammonium salts is decreased relative to a designated control.

label.value: abolished resistance to quaternary ammonium salt antimicrobial agent

value.value: A decreased resistance to quaternary ammonium salts where resistance to quaternary ammonium salts is abolished.
An absence of  motility phenotype where a microbe is not capable of gliding motility.
An absence of motility phenotype where a microbe is not capable of swarming motility.
An absence of motility phenotype where a microbe is not capable of swimming motility.
An absence of motility phenotype where a microbe is not capable of twitching motility.
A motility by gliding phenotype where the frequency, rate, timing, or extent of gliding is altered relative to a designated control.
A cell motility by twitching phenotype where the frequency, rate, timing, or extent of twitching is altered relative to a designated control.
A decreased motility by twitching phenotype where the ability of a microbe to move by twitching motility is abolished.
An antimicrobial resistance phenotype relating to resistance or sensitivity to an epoxide. An epoxide is any cyclic ether in which the oxygen atom forms part of a 3-membered ring.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: An epoxide resistance phenotype where an organism, cell, or cells is resistant to an epoxide.
An epoxide resistance phenotype where an organism or cell is sensitive to an epoxide.
An epoxide resistance phenotype where the frequency, rate, timing, or extent of resistance to an epoxide is altered relative to a designated control.
An altered epoxide resistance phenotype where the frequency, rate, timing, or extent of resistance to epoxide is increased relative to a designated control.
An altered epoxide resistance phenotype where the frequency, rate, timing, or extent of resistance to an epoxide is decreased relative to a designated control.
A decreased resistance to an epoxide phenotype where resistance to an epoxide is abolished.
A capsule morphology phenotype where the size, shape, or appearance of the capsule is altered relative to a designated control.
An altered capsule morphology phenotype where the size of the capsule is altered relative to a designated control.
An altered capsule size phenotype where the size of the capsule is increased relative to a designated control.
An altered capsule size phenotype where the size of the capsule is decreased relative to a designated control.

A cell morphology phenotype relating to the form and structure of titan cells, which are large vegetative cells produced by fungi that typically exhibit altered capsule structure, a thickened cell wall, increased ploidy, and resistance to nitrosative and oxidative stresses.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

value.value: A titan cell phenotype where a microbe is able to form titan cells.
A titan cell phenotype where a microbe cannot form titan cells.
A titan cell phenotype where the size, shape, or appearance of titan cells is altered relative to a designated control.
A titan cell formation phenotype where the frequency, rate, timing, or extent of titan cell formation is altered relative to a designated control.

A spore morphology phenotype that is related to the form and structure of an ascospore, which is a thick-walled spore that stores and protects one or more nuclei following sexual reproduction in an Ascomycete.
An ascospore morphology phenotype in which the form and structure of an ascospore is altered relative to a designated control.
An endospore morphology phenotype where the form and structure of an endospore is altered relative to a designated control.
A decreased osmotaxis phenotype where negative osmotaxis by a motile microbe is decreased relative to a designated control.
A decreased osmotaxis phenotype where positive osmotaxis by a motile microbe is decreased relative to a designated control.

label.value: population growth in high osmolarity phenotype

value.value: A population growth phenotype relating to the vegetative growth of a microbial population in conditions of high osmolarity, which refers to osmotic conditions where the osmolarity of the environment is higher than the osmolarity that allows for optimal population growth. Population growth may refer to growth rate, growth yield, or both.

label.value: presence of population growth in high osmolarity

value.value: A population growth phenotype where a microbial population can grow in conditions of high osmolarity.

label.value: absence of population growth in high osmolarity

value.value: A population growth phenotype where a microbial population doesn't grow in conditions of high osmolarity.

label.value: altered population growth in high osmolarity

value.value: A population growth phenotype where the growth of a microbial population in conditions of high osmolarity is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: increased population growth in high osmolarity

value.value: An altered population growth in high osmolarity phenotype where growth of a microbial population in conditions of high osmolarity is increased relative to a designated control. Increased growth may reflect an increased growth rate (i.e., faster growth), increased growth yield, or both.

label.value: decreased population growth in high osmolarity

value.value: An altered growth in high osmolarity phenotype where growth of a microbial population in high osmolarity is decreased relative to a designated control. Decreased growth may reflect a reduced growth rate (i.e., slower growth), reduced growth yield, or both.

label.value: abolished population growth in high osmolarity

value.value: A decreased population growth in high osmolarity phenotype where growth of the microbial population is abolished in conditions of high osmolarity.
A population growth range phenotype where the rate and/or extent of growth of a microbial population in a specified environmental condition is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: presence of lethality in an invertebrate host

value.value: A presence of lethality phenotype where infection by a microbe can cause death of an invertebrate host.

label.value: absence of lethality in an invertebrate host

value.value: An absence of lethality phenotype where the infected host is an invertebrate.

label.value: altered lethality in an invertebrate host

value.value: An altered lethality phenotype where the ability of an infectious  microbe to cause death of an invertebrate host is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: altered lethality in an amoeba host

value.value: An altered lethality phenotype where the ability of an infectious microbe to cause death of an amoeba host is altered relative to a designated control.

label.value: presence of lethality in an amoeba host

value.value: A presence of lethality phenotype where infection by a microbe can cause death of an amoeba host.

label.value: absence of lethality in an amoeba host

value.value: An absence of lethality phenotype where infection by a microbe doesn't cause death of an amoeba host.

label.value: decreased lethality in an amoeba host

value.value: An altered lethality in an amoeba host phenotype where the ability of an infectious microbe to cause death of an amoeba host is decreased relative to a designated control.

label.value: increased lethality in an amoeba host

value.value: An altered lethality in an amoeba phenotype where the ability of an infectious microbe to cause death of an amoeba host is increased relative to a designated control.

label.value: abolished lethality in an amoeba host

value.value: A decreased lethality in an amoeba host phenotype where the ability of an infectious microbe to cause death of an amoeba host is abolished.
